      {
        "id": "4160a6f1ba2dd568b21c06d9271adeb361bcb142",
        "author": {
          "account_id": 3239,
          "name": "Ram Krishna Verma",
          "display_name": null,
          "email": "ramkrishna.verma@gmail.com",
          "username": "ramverma"
        },
        "author_role": "REVIEWER",
        "timestamp": "2018-10-31 14:10:10.000000000",
        "message": "Patch Set 1:\n\n> Ram, Michael - can you help me fill this in? I've been digging into\n > the jobs. But still not exactly clear on what command to do this\n > locally.\n\nFor apex-pdp, I feel the process is similar to drools-pdp using the script at /apex-pdp/docker_build.sh to generate the image. The command in script is - \"docker build --quiet ${PROXY_ARGS} $TAGS packages/apex-pdp-docker/target/$IMAGE\"\n\nFor distribution, I think we are using the maven-docker-plugin for building the image. So one need to run the command - \"mvn clean deploy -B -P docker -Dmaven.test.skip=true\" to generate the image.\n\nMichael, please correct me if I am wrong.",
        "patchset_number": 1
      },
